<p>The AI model file is downloaded once over Wi-Fi from
    <a href="https://huggingface.co/">Hugging Face</a>. This download is a one-way transfer of a static file — we do not log
        your identity, IP address, or device identifiers in connection with this download beyond what the App Store and Google
        Play infrastructure inherently processes (see Apple's and Google's privacy policies for details).</p>
<h2>3. Crash reporting</h2>
<p>NobodyWho Chat uses
    <a href="https://sentry.io/">Sentry</a>, a third-party crash-reporting service, to collect anonymous crash diagnostics.
        If the app crashes or encounters a fatal error, Sentry receives a technical report so we can find and fix bugs.</p>
<p>These crash reports contain only non-personal technical information such as the type of error, the line of code where
    it occurred, the app version, the operating system version, and the device model. They do
    <strong>not</strong>
    contain your prompts, your messages, AI responses, your conversation history, your name, your email, or any other
    information that could identify you personally.</p>
<p>Crash data is processed by Sentry on our behalf and is used solely to diagnose and fix stability problems. Sentry's
    handling of this data is governed by
    <a href="https://sentry.io/privacy/">Sentry's Privacy Policy</a>. We do not use
            crash data for advertising, profiling, or any purpose other than improving the app.</p>
<h2>4. How the app works</h2>
<p>NobodyWho Chat runs a language model entirely on your device's processor. When you type or dictate a message, your
    input is processed on your device's chip, a response is generated on your device's chip, and the result is displayed on
    your device's screen.</p>
<p>At no point in this chain does any of your conversation data travel over a network. There are no API calls to
    external AI services, no relay servers, and no logging of your prompts or responses. Your messages are never used for
    crash reporting.</p>
<p>Once the AI model is downloaded, the app functions with no internet connection. You can use it on a plane in airplane
    mode, in a remote wilderness, or anywhere without cellular or Wi-Fi coverage. (Crash reports, when they occur, are sent
    the next time your device has a network connection.)</p>
<h2>5. Data sharing &amp; third parties</h2>
<p>We share no personal data with any third party, because we collect none. There are no advertising SDKs, no analytics
    platforms, and no data brokers involved in the operation of this app.</p>
<p>The third-party relationships relevant to this app are:</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Apple</strong>
        and
        <strong>Google</strong>, which distribute the app through the App Store and Google Play and process your purchase. Their
            data practices are governed by
        <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/">Apple's Privacy Policy</a>
        and
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.</li>
    <li>
        <strong>Sentry</strong>, which processes anonymous crash diagnostics on our behalf, as described in section 3.</li>
</ul>
<p>We do not sell, rent, license, or trade any user data.</p>
<h2>6. Children's privacy</h2>
<p>NobodyWho Chat does not knowingly collect any personal information from anyone, including children under the age of
    13 (or the applicable age in your jurisdiction). Since we collect no personal data, no special handling is required —
    though parents should be aware that, like any general-purpose AI assistant, the app's outputs may occasionally be
    unsuitable for young children.</p>
<h2>7. Security</h2>
<p>Because your conversation data never leaves your device, traditional concerns about server-side data breaches,
    unauthorized access, or data interception in transit do not apply to your prompts and messages.</p>
<p>Data stored on your device (such as saved conversations, if you choose to retain them) is protected by your
    platform's on-device encryption and is subject to your device's passcode and biometric protections. We encourage you to
    keep your device updated with the latest software.</p>
<h2>8. Your rights</h2>
<p>Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights including access, correction, deletion, or portability of
    personal data. Because NobodyWho Chat holds no personal data about you on any server, and crash reports are anonymous
    and cannot be tied to you, there is nothing personally identifying for us to provide, correct, or delete on our end.</p>
<p>Any conversations or data stored locally on your device can be deleted by uninstalling the app from your device, or
    by clearing app data through your device's settings. This is entirely within your control.</p>
<h2>9. Data retention</h2>
<p>We retain no personal user data. Any conversations stored on-device persist only as long as you choose to keep them,
    and uninstalling the app removes all app data from your device. Anonymous crash diagnostics are retained by Sentry
    according to its standard retention schedule and are used only to diagnose stability issues.</p>
<h2>10. Changes to this policy</h2>
<p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the "Last updated" date at the top of
    this page. If we ever make material changes — particularly any change that would result in us collecting data that we
    currently do not — we will notify you prominently within the app.</p>
<p>Your continued use of NobodyWho Chat after any changes constitutes your acceptance of the revised policy.</p>
